<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1833,2038]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1905,1930]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
The great resemblance between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vanhoffen" authorityYear="1910" box="[713,969,1905,1930]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="antarcticum">
<emphasis box="[713,969,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Halecium antarcticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pena Cantero" authorityYear="2014" box="[1036,1289,1905,1930]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pseudodelicatulum">
<emphasis box="[1036,1289,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">H. pseudodelicatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes both species almost indistinguishable in the absence of gonothecae (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero, A. L." box="[918,1153,1941,1966]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="243 - 280" refId="ref44359" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. (2014 b) Revision of the Antarctic species of Halecium Oken, 1815 (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Haleciidae). Zootaxa, 3790 (2), 243 - 280. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3790.2.2" type="journal article" year="2014">Peña Cantero 2014b</bibRefCitation>
). The material examined here has been tentatively assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vanhoffen" authorityYear="1910" box="[584,754,1978,2001]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="antarcticum">
<emphasis box="[584,754,1978,2001]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">H. antarcticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the disposition of the hydrophore, pointing more outwards than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pena Cantero" authorityYear="2014" box="[344,591,2013,2038]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pseudodelicatulum">
<emphasis box="[344,591,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">H. pseudodelicatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[605,722,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1636,1658]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,344,1609]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[150,1436,339,1615]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 13. a Halecium cf. antarcticum: hydrophore and hydrotheca. b–d H. banzare: b hydrophore and hydrotheca; c male gonotheca; d colony. e H. exaggeratum: hydrophore and hydrotheca. f–g H. incertus: f hydrophore and hydrotheca; g gonotheca. h H. interpolatum: hydrophore and hydrotheca. i H. jaederholmi: hydrophore and hydrotheca. j–k H. pseudodelicatulum: j hydrophore and hydrotheca; k female gonotheca. l H. pseudoincertus: hydrophore and hydrotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608553/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 13a, j</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,151,176]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Ecology and distribution.</emphasis>
Species reported from 45 (
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, J. E." box="[808,959,152,176]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="165 - 178" refId="ref47732" refString="Watson, J. E. (2008) Hydroids of the BANZARE expeditions, 1929 - 1931: the family Haleciidae (Hydrozoa, Leptothecata) from the Australian Antarctic Territory. Memoirs of the Museum of Fictoria, 65, 165 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2008.65.9" type="journal article" year="2008">Watson 2008</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<quantity box="[1003,1088,151,176]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.157" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="1157.0">1157 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero, A. L." box="[1102,1336,152,176]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="1711 - 1731" refId="ref44300" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. (2014 a) Benthic hydroids (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa) from the continental shelf and slope off Queen Mary Coast (East Antarctica). Polar Biology, 37, 1711 - 1731. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00300 - 014 - 1556 - 0" type="journal article" year="2014">Peña Cantero 2014a</bibRefCitation>
); present material was collected between 254 and 
<specimenCount box="[613,692,188,213]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="generic">
<quantity box="[613,688,188,213]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.58" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="758.0">758 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
Species reported exclusively from East 
<collectingCountry box="[1151,1268,188,213]" name="Antarctica" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero, A. L." pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="243 - 280" refId="ref44359" refString="Pena Cantero, A. L. (2014 b) Revision of the Antarctic species of Halecium Oken, 1815 (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa, Haleciidae). Zootaxa, 3790 (2), 243 - 280. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3790.2.2" type="journal article" year="2014">Peña Cantero 2014b</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, if confirmed, present record will constitute the first evidence from the Weddell Sea as well as for West 
<collectingCountry box="[213,333,260,285]" name="Antarctica" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
, pointing to a circum-Antarctic distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
